340 g Pizza Dough
250 g Mild Italian Sausage, uncased
½ cup Marinara Sauce
¼ cup Roasted Pepper Pesto
¾ cup Mozzarella Cheese, shredded
113 g Mushrooms
1 tbsp Garlic Spread
56 g Spring Mix
2 tbsp Caesar Dressing
¼ cup Parmesan Cheese, shredded
28 g Croutons
113 g Baby Heirloom Tomatoes
0.06 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*

Thinly slice mushrooms.
Sprinkle both sides of dough with flour. Stretch into a rough oval shape on a parchment-lined baking sheet. (NOTE: For 4 ppl, use 2 parchment-lined baking sheets.) Let dough rest in a warm place for 8-10 min.

Meanwhile, heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high heat. When hot, add half the garlic spread, then sausage and mushrooms. Cook, breaking up sausage into smaller pieces, until no pink remains and mushrooms are tender, 4-5 min.** Season with salt and pepper. (NOTE: Don't overcrowd the pan; cook patties in 2 batches if needed.)
Using a slotted spoon, transfer to a paper towel-lined plate.

With floured hands, stretch dough again into a large 9x13 rectangle. (NOTE: The dough should now hold its shape.)
Spread pesto over dough, keeping a 1-inch border around all sides. Top with sausage, mushrooms, half the Parmesan and mozzarella.
Slowly roll one long end tightly over the filling, making sure to finish with the seam on the bottom. (TIP: If things get sticky, just dust your hands with a bit of flour!)
Pinch ends, then tuck under the roll.
Brush top with remaining garlic spread, then cut three slits into the top.

Bake stromboli in the middle of the oven until golden-brown, 18-25 min. (NOTE: For 4 ppl, bake stombolis in the middle and top of the oven, rotating sheets halfway through.)

Meanwhile, halve tomatoes.
Add spring mix, tomatoes, remaining Parmesan and croutons to a large bowl.
Drizzle Caesar dressing over top. Season with pepper, then toss to combine.

Once stomboli is baked through, let cool slightly on the baking sheet, 5 min.
Meanwhile, heat marinara in the microwave until warmed through, 1 min.
Using a serrated knife, slice stromboli into 8 equal pieces.
Divide salad and stromboli between plates.
Serve marinara on the side for dipping.